{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"283d0bf4-8010-4822-ad8c-14c5a6f2e9b8","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces the old framework + adapter + test SDK)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed — `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and the `Assert` API are all still supported under the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n- Remove the `<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />` line\n- Replace `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with a single `MSTest` v3 package (it bundles the test SDK, framework, and adapter)\n\nWant me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"507de83d-7a20-4a7b-8242-449eee83fd67","outputTokens":334,"requestId":"BC2A:48F1C:2156414:250F2DB:69FAA636"},"id":"8abbf9ae-4f0e-4b11-bbf3-e216e480a0c7","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:23:57.273Z","parentId":"db3815e2-718b-42ef-9fbe-759820b28173"}
